00:23:11.681 --> 00:23:14.267
[Hwa-jin] Damn it. Why didn't you
press the button. you punk?

491
00:23:15.727 --> 00:23:17.979
-Thank you. Goodbye. Till next time.
-[Jun-hyeong groans]

492
00:23:18.063 --> 00:23:19.606
-Let go!
-[Hwa-jin] Where's the entrance?

493
00:23:19.689 --> 00:23:21.983
-[electronic voice] <i>Doors closing.</i>
-These doors are slow.

494
00:23:22.067 --> 00:23:23.944
[tense music continues]

495
00:23:28.824 --> 00:23:31.159
Would you look
at how clean the whole bathroom is.

496
00:23:31.243 --> 00:23:33.036
You did a very nice job.

497
00:23:33.870 --> 00:23:35.622
I can see my reflection down there.

498
00:23:36.540 --> 00:23:38.625
You're good when you want to be. Okay.

499
00:23:38.708 --> 00:23:41.711
Once you're done here. leave the cleaning
supplies just like you found them.

500
00:23:41.795 --> 00:23:43.880
All right? [clears throat]

501
00:23:46.758 --> 00:23:47.926
[ominous music plays]

502
00:23:48.009 --> 00:23:50.011
[breathes deeply]

503
00:23:51.888 --> 00:23:52.973
[grunts]

504
00:23:53.056 --> 00:23:54.057
[music stops]

505
00:23:55.267 --> 00:23:57.269
STUDENT RECORD

506
00:23:57.352 --> 00:24:01.565
STUDENT NAME: PARK DAE-SEOK

507
00:24:06.820 --> 00:24:08.405
Choi Gang-seok.

508
00:24:10.824 --> 00:24:13.076
I've just learned
that the Minister of Education

509
00:24:13.160 --> 00:24:14.995
is the founder of the ERPB.

510
00:24:15.078 --> 00:24:17.247
I've also learned
that you are not a licensed teacher.

511
00:24:17.330 --> 00:24:20.584
I have been given the title of teacher
until the end of our inquiry.

512
00:24:20.667 --> 00:24:22.252
But I'm sure you already knew that.

513
00:24:23.211 --> 00:24:25.505
There is something
I need your help clarifying.

514
00:24:25.589 --> 00:24:27.257
How did my Jun-hyeong bruise his head?

515
00:24:28.175 --> 00:24:29.551
I'm not sure what to say.

516
00:24:29.634 --> 00:24:32.554
I told him to clean the bowl.
but I never said to smash his head on it.

517
00:24:32.637 --> 00:24:35.891
Are you saying he deliberately inflicted
an injury on himself just to frame you?

518
00:24:35.974 --> 00:24:37.726
I know he finds it's easy to hurt others.

519
00:24:37.809 --> 00:24:40.103
but can you imagine
how terrified he was of hurting himself?

520
00:24:40.187 --> 00:24:41.646
And that bruise of his.

521
00:24:41.730 --> 00:24:43.273
doesn't it look a little staged?

522
00:24:43.356 --> 00:24:49.362
[Gwang-pil laughs]

523
00:24:52.908 --> 00:24:54.409
Seems you're the one who's not afraid.

524
00:24:54.493 --> 00:24:57.120
Let's imagine a doctor
who's afraid of their patients.

525
00:24:57.204 --> 00:24:58.663
He'd be unable to treat them.

526
00:24:59.706 --> 00:25:02.083
Now if you imagine a lawyer
who's afraid of their clients.

527
00:25:02.167 --> 00:25:03.627
he couldn't represent them. could he?

528
00:25:03.710 --> 00:25:04.878
[tense music plays]

529
00:25:04.961 --> 00:25:08.089
And lastly. if a teacher
were afraid of their students.

530
00:25:08.882 --> 00:25:10.926
would they be able to teach them properly?

531
00:25:11.009 --> 00:25:12.135
-[chuckles]
-[Gwang-pil] Oh.

532
00:25:13.678 --> 00:25:15.680
I'm sure you're well aware

533
00:25:16.723 --> 00:25:18.725
of what it means
that I'm standing here today.

534
00:25:22.062 --> 00:25:24.981
The ERPB is a national organization.

535
00:25:26.107 --> 00:25:27.901
You'd be picking a pretty big fight.

536
00:25:27.984 --> 00:25:31.196
-That's my field of expertise.
-[Hwa-jin] That's good to know.

537
00:25:48.880 --> 00:25:49.839
[music fades]

538
00:25:52.300 --> 00:25:55.095
We heard that you reported us
to the Bureau. you fucking bitch.

539
00:25:56.012 --> 00:25:58.098
-It wasn't me.
-Don't fucking lie to us.

540
00:25:58.181 --> 00:26:01.142
You know how busy Jun-hyeong's father is?
You made him come all the way here.

541
00:26:01.226 --> 00:26:04.396
-You wanna meet Dae-seok that bad?
-I swear it wasn't me. I didn't call 'em.

542
00:26:05.313 --> 00:26:07.440
-You motherfucker.
-[Gwang-su] Hey. hey. hey.

543
00:26:07.524 --> 00:26:09.025
-It wasn't you?
-[Gyeong-min coughs]

544
00:26:09.109 --> 00:26:12.279
[Jun-hyeong] I don't fucking care if you
were the one who called. You're gonna pay.

545
00:26:12.362 --> 00:26:13.238
[Gyeong-min groans]

546
00:26:13.321 --> 00:26:15.574
[Gwang-su] What did we do to you. huh?
You little punk.

547
00:26:15.657 --> 00:26:16.658
-[grunting]
-Let's leave.

548
00:26:16.741 --> 00:26:17.826
-Keep moving.
-[groaning]

549
00:26:17.909 --> 00:26:20.579
-[boy] I said keep moving.
-[Jun-hyeong] You stupid fuck.

550
00:26:20.662 --> 00:26:23.540
-[groans]
-[Gwang-su] Hey. lift your head. fucker.

551
00:26:24.207 --> 00:26:26.084
-[blows thud]
-[grunting]

552
00:26:26.167 --> 00:26:29.004
[Gwang-su] Hey. hey. Come on.
admit you called them.

553
00:26:29.087 --> 00:26:31.923
[breathes shakily]

554
00:26:32.007 --> 00:26:34.092
[somber music plays]

555
00:26:43.560 --> 00:26:47.772
[breathes shakily]

556
00:26:47.856 --> 00:26:49.107
[music fades]

557
00:26:49.858 --> 00:26:51.901
[gasps]

558
00:26:51.985 --> 00:26:54.362
[cries]

559
00:26:54.446 --> 00:26:56.740
Jeez. kid. you're a real handful.
aren't you?

560
00:26:56.823 --> 00:26:58.158
So. what do you want? Up or down?

561
00:26:58.241 --> 00:27:00.160
Up! Just pull me up!

562
00:27:00.243 --> 00:27:01.870
Hey. don't forget the magic word now.

563
00:27:01.953 --> 00:27:05.081
Please pull me up! [panicked breathing]

564
00:27:05.874 --> 00:27:07.626
[grunts]

565
00:27:08.335 --> 00:27:11.254
[Gyeong-min panting]

566
00:27:17.302 --> 00:27:18.720
Come with me. [clears throat]

567
00:27:19.596 --> 00:27:20.680
[sighs]

568
00:27:25.477 --> 00:27:27.854
So it seems like
you're always getting beat up

569
00:27:27.937 --> 00:27:30.273
by Ryu Jun-hyeong and his boys.
Is that it?

570
00:27:33.193 --> 00:27:36.404
So. how long do you plan
on getting bullied and doing nothing. kid?

571
00:27:38.406 --> 00:27:40.659
Don't lecture me.
You don't know what you're talking about.

572
00:27:41.368 --> 00:27:45.330
You know what changes if I fight back?
Nothing. They'll just do it again.

573
00:27:45.413 --> 00:27:47.123
When did I tell you to fight back?

574
00:27:47.999 --> 00:27:49.084
I'm just telling you to run.

575
00:27:50.377 --> 00:27:52.128
Listen. if anyone tells you to fight back.

576
00:27:52.212 --> 00:27:54.839
then clearly they've never been beat up
by a group of guys before.

577
00:27:56.216 --> 00:27:57.509
Then they'd beat me again.

578
00:27:57.592 --> 00:27:58.885
Then you just run away again.

579
00:27:58.968 --> 00:28:00.845
I can't just run forever.

580
00:28:01.346 --> 00:28:04.015
That's true.
You can't just keep running away.

581
00:28:04.099 --> 00:28:05.266
So. then.

582
00:28:06.184 --> 00:28:07.602
go and speak with an adult.

583
00:28:08.228 --> 00:28:09.646
And what good will that do?

584
00:28:09.729 --> 00:28:12.399
You'll never know until you ask. [tuts]

585
00:28:14.234 --> 00:28:15.902
There are good adults out there.

586
00:28:20.699 --> 00:28:22.325
So. Gyeong-min. from now on.

587
00:28:22.826 --> 00:28:25.954
you are going to learn
to run as fast as possible.

588
00:28:26.621 --> 00:28:28.123
See that soccer goal over there?

589
00:28:28.623 --> 00:28:30.583
You've got ten seconds to make it back.

590
00:28:31.501 --> 00:28:33.044
-Sir?
-Run.

591
00:28:33.128 --> 00:28:35.463
Are you deaf? Run!

592
00:28:35.547 --> 00:28:38.258
Come on. faster than that!
This the fastest you can run?

593
00:28:38.758 --> 00:28:40.468
Keep slacking
and I'll set the dogs on you.

594
00:28:40.552 --> 00:28:43.388
-[Gyeong-min] There's a dog here?
-[Hwa-jin] Yeah. me! I'm the wild dog.

595
00:28:44.097 --> 00:28:45.432
-Hurry up. kid!
-[Gyeong-min] Okay!

596
00:28:45.515 --> 00:28:47.517
[gentle music plays]

597
00:28:48.518 --> 00:28:50.520
Gyeong-min. think you can manage
on your own?

598
00:28:50.603 --> 00:28:53.440
-Yes. sir.
-[Hwa-jin] Damn right. You got it.

599
00:28:54.399 --> 00:28:56.818
You did a good job today.
Thank you very much.

600
00:28:57.902 --> 00:28:59.904
Look at that presentation.

601
00:28:59.988 --> 00:29:02.532
I think you might've learned
a thing or two from being bullied.

602
00:29:03.658 --> 00:29:05.243
So you're just like them. sir.

603
00:29:05.326 --> 00:29:06.828
That's where you'd be wrong.

604
00:29:06.911 --> 00:29:09.748
They're just bullies.
I'm a teacher who cares.

605
00:29:09.831 --> 00:29:10.915
[music stops]

606
00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:13.585
They're not just bullies though.

607
00:29:14.335 --> 00:29:16.296
They've got power and influence.

608
00:29:17.922 --> 00:29:19.674
Do you know Jun-hyeong's father?

609
00:29:19.758 --> 00:29:21.676
He can ruin an entire family just for fun.

610
00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:23.803
Don't worry about his father. all right?

611
00:29:24.804 --> 00:29:26.389
I've got my own powerful allies.

612
00:29:27.724 --> 00:29:29.684
I'm glad you have people to rely on.

613
00:29:29.768 --> 00:29:30.852
[chuckles]

614
00:29:31.978 --> 00:29:32.937
Gyeong-min.

615
00:29:33.980 --> 00:29:36.024
you know. you also have
people you can rely on.

616
00:29:37.734 --> 00:29:38.735
Like who?

617
00:29:41.571 --> 00:29:42.614
What do you mean?

618
00:29:43.698 --> 00:29:45.450
So. no one comes to mind?

619
00:29:46.701 --> 00:29:48.536
Come on. kid. Think a bit.

620
00:29:51.873 --> 00:29:52.999
[sighs]

621
00:29:53.500 --> 00:29:56.503
Jeez. you're a student.
There's only one answer. Teachers.

622
00:29:57.295 --> 00:29:59.380
Are you kidding me?
Weren't you listening earlier?

623
00:29:59.881 --> 00:30:01.424
Look. I can be pretty reliable.

624
00:30:02.091 --> 00:30:04.803
-I peeled this just for you.
-[Gyeong-min] Oh. thank you. sir.

625
00:30:04.886 --> 00:30:06.513
[Hwa-jin laughs]

626
00:30:08.097 --> 00:30:09.307
[Hwa-jin sighs]

627
00:30:10.683 --> 00:30:13.520
So. Gyeong-min. you're telling me
you went through all of high school

628
00:30:13.603 --> 00:30:15.480
without making a friend. huh?

629
00:30:18.358 --> 00:30:20.235
I haven't always been the outcast.

630
00:30:23.947 --> 00:30:25.782
How come you didn't tell your parents?

631
00:30:26.324 --> 00:30:28.076
Were you worried about how they'd react?

632
00:30:32.247 --> 00:30:33.832
[melancholy music plays]

633
00:30:37.043 --> 00:30:43.967
DARLING SON
ENJOY YOUR DAY!

634
00:30:48.638 --> 00:30:50.181
Huh. who knows?

635
00:30:50.765 --> 00:30:53.226
Just eat your <i>ramyeon </i>while it's warm.

636
00:30:56.437 --> 00:30:57.689
[Gyeong-min slurps]

637
00:30:59.232 --> 00:31:00.233
All right.

638
00:31:13.746 --> 00:31:17.041
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

639
00:31:17.125 --> 00:31:18.251
[music stops]

640
00:31:19.210 --> 00:31:21.796
[woman] Oh. uh. sir.
you can't go in there!

641
00:31:24.841 --> 00:31:28.678
Oh. To what do I owe
this pleasure. Congressman Ryu?

642
00:31:28.761 --> 00:31:31.264
This Protection Bureau thing.

643
00:31:31.347 --> 00:31:33.016
is it true you're the one behind all this?

644
00:31:33.600 --> 00:31:34.559
[chuckles]

645
00:31:35.059 --> 00:31:36.102
[sighs]

646
00:31:38.104 --> 00:31:40.148
Well. yes. I am.

647
00:31:40.732 --> 00:31:41.983
How about a cup of tea?

648
00:31:42.483 --> 00:31:44.485
I didn't come here to drink tea with you.

649
00:31:44.569 --> 00:31:45.445
[minister chuckles]

650
00:31:46.946 --> 00:31:49.449
Why don't you
come and sit down? [chuckles]

651
00:31:52.368 --> 00:31:54.829
Minister. why did you feel the need
to create this thing?

652
00:31:54.913 --> 00:31:55.830
[tuts]

653
00:31:56.414 --> 00:31:59.208
[sighs] I did it because I had to.

654
00:32:00.209 --> 00:32:02.128
I'm sure I don't have to remind you

655
00:32:02.754 --> 00:32:05.840
of the teacher
who was murdered two years ago.

656
00:32:05.924 --> 00:32:08.343
That teacher was killed by her student.

657
00:32:09.052 --> 00:32:11.638
The reason I created
the Education Rights Protection Bureau

658
00:32:11.721 --> 00:32:14.057
was to ensure that such a tragedy
never happened again.

659
00:32:14.140 --> 00:32:16.017
But why send them to Daehan High School?

660
00:32:16.100 --> 00:32:19.270
My son is now being harassed
by one of your inspectors.

661
00:32:19.354 --> 00:32:21.606
Are you telling me
your son attends Daehan High School?

662
00:32:23.316 --> 00:32:25.568
Why. I wasn't aware. [chuckles]

663
00:32:26.069 --> 00:32:29.030
Do you know what your so-called inspector
has been doing at the school?

664
00:32:29.113 --> 00:32:31.032
If it went public. we'd all be in trouble.

665
00:32:31.115 --> 00:32:34.243
Nothing good can come of this. so let's
end this quietly while we still can.

666
00:32:35.328 --> 00:32:36.371
[clears throat]

667
00:32:37.121 --> 00:32:40.375
You see. it's just
that we've only just started.

668
00:32:40.458 --> 00:32:43.294
and founding this organization
was no easy task.

669
00:32:43.378 --> 00:32:45.296
How about we give it a chance first?

670
00:32:45.380 --> 00:32:48.424
Minister Gang-seok. you know
how much I respect you. don't you?

671
00:32:48.508 --> 00:32:49.467
[chuckles]

672
00:32:49.550 --> 00:32:51.803
[Gwang-pil] I'm saying this
with all the care in the world.

673
00:32:51.886 --> 00:32:55.431
It'd be a terrible shame for you to retire
over something so mundane.

674
00:32:55.515 --> 00:32:57.934
[chuckles]

675
00:33:01.562 --> 00:33:03.398
A father helping his son

676
00:33:04.190 --> 00:33:05.817
must never be taken lightly.

677
00:33:11.990 --> 00:33:13.116
[door opens]

678
00:33:14.242 --> 00:33:15.201
[door closes]

679
00:33:16.995 --> 00:33:20.248
[man 1] Welcome to Congressman
Ryu Gwang-pil's Happy Hope Party.

680
00:33:20.331 --> 00:33:22.875
-Thank you for your support.
-[woman 1] Thank you for your support.

681
00:33:22.959 --> 00:33:24.877
-What time is it?
-[woman 2] Take a book.

682
00:33:24.961 --> 00:33:28.131
-Till next time.
-How about a bit of professionalism?

683
00:33:28.214 --> 00:33:29.090
Sorry about that.

684
00:33:29.173 --> 00:33:31.509
â€œPeople as people. politics as politicsâ€

685
00:33:31.592 --> 00:33:32.885
-[cell phone chimes]
-What's this?

686
00:33:32.969 --> 00:33:35.054
â€œUsing aides for personal matters?â€

687
00:33:35.138 --> 00:33:37.932
[man 2] Bribes of valuables
in exchange for local election nomination?

688
00:33:38.016 --> 00:33:39.475
[woman 3] Sexual harassment?

689
00:33:39.559 --> 00:33:42.729
[crowd] Ryu Gwang-pil!
Ryu Gwang-pil! Ryu Gwang-pil!

690
00:33:42.812 --> 00:33:44.731
[Gwang-pil] Thank you.
So glad you could make it.

691
00:33:44.814 --> 00:33:47.775
-[man 3] You've got my vote.
-I know you're busy. Thank you for coming.

692
00:33:47.859 --> 00:33:50.570
What do you have to say
about the allegations of bribery?

693
00:33:50.653 --> 00:33:51.988
An anonymous tip was just released

694
00:33:52.071 --> 00:33:54.282
regarding your sexual harassment
of female colleagues.

695
00:33:54.365 --> 00:33:57.618
[woman 4] Information has been released
on your use of government property.

696
00:33:57.702 --> 00:33:59.871
What the hell is going on right now?

697
00:33:59.954 --> 00:34:00.872
[reporters clamor]

698
00:34:00.955 --> 00:34:02.415
[woman 5] Congressman Gwang-pil!

699
00:34:02.498 --> 00:34:04.542
[man 4] What does this mean
for your campaign?

700
00:34:05.126 --> 00:34:06.878
-Stay back! Stay back!
-Congressman Gwang-pil!

701
00:34:06.961 --> 00:34:09.255
[tense music plays]

702
00:34:09.338 --> 00:34:10.965
Goddamn it.

703
00:34:13.426 --> 00:34:14.844
What the hell's going on?

704
00:34:29.609 --> 00:34:30.526
[music fades]

705
00:34:39.786 --> 00:34:40.620
[sighs]

706
00:34:44.540 --> 00:34:45.458
[Gwang-pil scoffs]

707
00:34:48.419 --> 00:34:51.172
Is everything all right?
What's all the commotion?

708
00:34:51.255 --> 00:34:52.840
[Gwang-pil] Don't worry. It's nothing.

709
00:34:53.549 --> 00:34:55.551
Now if you'll excuse me. I have to go.

710
00:34:57.303 --> 00:35:01.349
[Gang-seok] Our dear Congressman Ryu
doesn't seem to fully grasp his situation.

711
00:35:02.683 --> 00:35:04.685
[tense music plays]

712
00:35:09.774 --> 00:35:10.691
[chuckles]

713
00:35:11.859 --> 00:35:13.069
Wait a minute.

714
00:35:14.320 --> 00:35:16.489
Are you the one who leaked all of this?

715
00:35:16.572 --> 00:35:18.783
Why the hell are you doing this to me?!

716
00:35:18.866 --> 00:35:20.868
[haunting music plays]

717
00:35:27.792 --> 00:35:29.836
Did you know it took me two years

718
00:35:31.420 --> 00:35:33.172
to establish the Bureau.

719
00:35:34.423 --> 00:35:38.386
And it turns out
that you can learn a lot in two years.

720
00:35:49.105 --> 00:35:51.607
RYU GWANG-PIL
UNOFFICIAL REPORT

721
00:35:53.359 --> 00:35:54.861
RECORDING OF VICTIM INTERVIEW

722
00:35:59.115 --> 00:36:01.075
RYU GWANG-PIL
NOMINATION CORRUPTION REPORT

723
00:36:03.995 --> 00:36:05.079
[music fades]

724
00:36:05.163 --> 00:36:08.833
Are you insane? By doing this to me.
you will ruin our party!

725
00:36:09.333 --> 00:36:11.544
We are both on the same side!

726
00:36:12.044 --> 00:36:13.379
That's where you're wrong.

727
00:36:13.880 --> 00:36:17.300
There are no sides
when we talk about education.

728
00:36:17.383 --> 00:36:19.844
I knew it.
You were targeting me from the start.

729
00:36:19.927 --> 00:36:21.053
What did I do wrong?

730
00:36:21.137 --> 00:36:23.514
I did more for this party
than anyone else did!

731
00:36:23.598 --> 00:36:25.516
You still think this is about the party?

732
00:36:26.142 --> 00:36:28.936
As for what you did wrong.
well. I'm sure it'll be all over the news.

733
00:36:29.020 --> 00:36:30.521
[laughs]

734
00:36:30.605 --> 00:36:31.564
[roars]

735
00:36:31.647 --> 00:36:33.733
This isn't fucking fair!

736
00:36:33.816 --> 00:36:36.527
I've done nothing
compared to the rest of these scum.

737
00:36:36.611 --> 00:36:39.030
so why would you ever do this to me?

738
00:36:47.205 --> 00:36:49.332
Because you needed to fall

739
00:36:50.458 --> 00:36:51.667
for your son

740
00:36:53.127 --> 00:36:54.754
to learn his lesson.

741
00:36:55.338 --> 00:36:57.340
[tense music plays]

742
00:37:00.384 --> 00:37:05.181
Really. you should have done a better job
at raising that child of yours.

743
00:37:07.975 --> 00:37:09.352
