Minister. Everyone. make room.

746
00:37:21.614 --> 00:37:22.990
[Gwang-pil] Goddamn it!

747
00:37:23.491 --> 00:37:26.202
-[reporter 1] That's him. isn't it?
-[reporters clamor]

748
00:37:26.786 --> 00:37:30.539
[reporter 2] <i>The National Assembly</i>
<i>approved a motion to arrest Ryu Gwang-pil.</i>

749
00:37:30.623 --> 00:37:34.669
<i>who is under investigation in connection</i>
<i>to multiple corruption allegations.</i>

750
00:37:34.752 --> 00:37:36.963
<i>Support for the motion increased</i>
<i>amid reports</i>

751
00:37:37.046 --> 00:37:39.799
<i>alleging that the congressman's son</i>
<i>was a notorious bully</i>

752
00:37:39.882 --> 00:37:42.426
<i>whose actions drove one of his victims</i>
<i>to take his own life.</i>

753
00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:44.220
<i>This case. which had nearly been buried.</i>

754
00:37:44.303 --> 00:37:48.349
<i>was uncovered by an investigation by</i>
<i>the Educational Rights Protection Bureau.</i>

755
00:37:48.432 --> 00:37:49.725
<i>a newly established agency</i>

756
00:37:49.809 --> 00:37:51.936
<i>under the direct authority</i>
<i>of the Minister of Education.</i>

757
00:37:52.019 --> 00:37:55.314
<i>The Bureau operates independently</i>
<i>and is responsible for receiving reports.</i>

758
00:37:55.398 --> 00:37:58.234
<i>conducting investigations</i>
<i>and responding to violation of conduct.</i>

759
00:38:00.987 --> 00:38:03.489
I'm starting to think
this will become a political issue.

760
00:38:04.240 --> 00:38:05.283
Will that be a problem?

761
00:38:05.366 --> 00:38:08.286
Don't you worry about that.
I'll make sure to bite the bullet.

762
00:38:08.869 --> 00:38:10.997
You just focus on getting the job done.

763
00:38:12.999 --> 00:38:15.459
What are you talking about.
"I'll bite the bullet"?

764
00:38:16.127 --> 00:38:18.671
Get back to me
once you've been in the line of fire.

765
00:38:19.964 --> 00:38:21.674
It was only a metaphor.

766
00:38:23.259 --> 00:38:24.635
You think I'm in the line of fire?

767
00:38:24.719 --> 00:38:26.387
No. I was just using a metaphor.

768
00:38:26.470 --> 00:38:27.763
Great job today.

769
00:38:29.974 --> 00:38:31.892
[laughs]

770
00:38:32.393 --> 00:38:35.187
[indistinct chatter]

771
00:38:39.817 --> 00:38:42.028
[boy 1] Hey. hey. hey.
Did you guys see this?

772
00:38:42.111 --> 00:38:44.780
[boy 2] <i>As of today.</i>
<i>the Daehan High outcast is</i>

773
00:38:44.864 --> 00:38:48.576
our adorable princess Jun-hyeong!
Congratulations!

774
00:38:48.659 --> 00:38:51.620
-I really think this fits you best.
-[Gwang-su] I think you're right.

775
00:38:51.704 --> 00:38:53.456
-[Jun-hyeong grunts]
-Oh! Oh!

776
00:38:54.540 --> 00:38:57.209
Oh. sweetheart. where are you going?
Huh? [laughs]

777
00:38:57.293 --> 00:38:59.712
Don't forget you're fucking nothing
without your dad!

778
00:38:59.795 --> 00:39:01.422
[boy 3] Looks like
the dumpster boy's back.

779
00:39:01.505 --> 00:39:02.715
-[laughter]
-[breathes heavily]

780
00:39:02.798 --> 00:39:05.926
OUTCAST STICK`

